title: Grateful Dead Live at The Scope on 1982-04-03
lineage: Cassette Master (Nakamichi DR-1) -> Sound Devices 744T (24bit/44.1k) -> Adobe Audition v3.0 -> Samplitude Professional v11.2 -> FLAC/16
description:
Set 1

Alabama Getaway-> Greatest Story Ever Told, They Love Each Other, Me & My Uncle-> Big River, Peggy-O-> CC Rider, Bird Song, It's All Over Now, Althea-> Let It Grow

Set 2

Scarlet Begonias-> Fire On The Mountain-> Estimated Prophet-> Eyes Of The World-> Good Time Blues-> Drums-> Not Fade Away-> Stella Blue-> One More Saturday Night, E: U.S. Blues

reviews.review_text: Bon Appetit' Excellent work fellas. Thanks - had the 2nd set on cassette as a youth - probably still have it, but pales next to this.  5 star show for 82 and 5 star for sound in comparison to the others - 41/2 star show in my ever evolving Dead rankings. Thanks again. Love it.
great recording real nice doped up Scarlet/Fire

Phenominal Recording This is a stellar recording folks - absolutely phenominal for an audience recording.   Hadn't heard it for years and thought I'd give it a spin.  The show is good, maybe 3 1/2 stars but, I wouldn't give more than four if I was stretching it.  Nice first set and good pre drums with quite possibly the best Never Trust A Woman Brent ever did... even thought I canned it as well as tossing a short and unimpressive NFA and OMSN to instead fade in Stella Blue from Eyes and fading in U.S. Blues from Stella in Soundforge music editing to make a very sweet ending.

I'm having a hard time justifying giving this show five stars simply because the capture is so fabulous. I'll say 4 1/2 stars.  But the two reviewers before me have done the job of wishing I could give it the highest rating.  Ah 1982, the last gasp of their prime years.
